fields.description:
Hi,

Regularly I check iTunes Connect to see any Crash Reports and now I've got a few with this strange crashes happening to some users...

PiniOn: WTI::Vector<WTI::RefPtr<TI::ProfileNode>, 0ul>::shrinkCapacity + 120342


Do you have any hints on why this would be happening? We  have extensively tested and stressed the app before publishing. This didn't happen on previous versions of the app (at least I saw no crash reports on iTunes Connect related to this, nor user complaints regarding crashes).

Some users are reporting problems in a particular window where we use image shrinking done by Ti.ImageFactory.compress on Ti.imagefactory module and generate thumbs using native blob functions such e.media.imageAsThumbnail and e.media.imageAsResized. We have used the very same functions and constructions since the beginning of the app and it never crashed the app.

Follows the complete crash:

fields.summary: iOS: Weird crash related to Ti:ProfileNode
fields.environment:
Seen on iOS 6.1.3 and 6.1.2
iPhone 4, 4S and 5
Titanium 3.0.0.GA

comments.body:
It could be module related - can you list all the modules you're using?

As you may know we open sourced the ImageFactory module, so you could try building the latest version against the SDK you're using: https://github.com/appcelerator/titanium_modules/tree/master/imagefactory

And of course, it might be good practice to update your SDK to 3.1 GA (though I'd maybe wait until 3.1.1 is out).
Resolving as needs more info for now.
